In realistic situations, the compounds are always in contact with a reactive environment, e.g., in an O2 (plus H2) atmosphere. Under such conditions, the oxidation of a metal (X) is described by the reaction pathn⋅X+m2⋅O2+l2H2→XnOmHl,\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
